One of the best food investments I have made is putting down the extra money
for the Weber Performer.
I fill the baskets, fire up the propane lighter, let it  burn for five
minutes, and one half hour later you're ready to go. It makes charcoal/wood
grilling as effortless as gas.
The current model has a real disadvanatage. It uses a disposable propane can
of fuel rather than the 5lb tank. The older tank lasts for at least 150
charcoal lights, or a whole season, and the disposable does 10-15, according
to Weber. I also wonder about it's flame output. It raises the cost of
lighting. I don't know if you can hitch a 20lb tank to the new one as you're
supposed to be able to with the old 5lb tank. I doubt it.
Cheers,

Kent
