You can bake ribs, but it is not the same as barbecue, and you will
never quite achieve that divinely smoky flavour we have all come to know
and love.

That said, they can still be good in their own right.  If I am going to
bake ribs, First, I remove the fell, then rub them down with the
seasoning/rub of your choice.  My personal favourite is Greek seasoning,
a mixture of salt, pepper, garlic, oregano and lemon rind.  I bake them
on a baking sheet in a slow oven about 300F - 325F until done. I might
baste them with lemon juice once or twice.

Not the same as barbecue, but still very tasty.

Abby

